docs.lead_paragraph: The sharp rise in the foreign exchanges on Saturday stood out as the most significant price movement of the week. After an early week business of light proportions and narrow fluctuations, higher cables from Europe on Saturday resulted in a turnover which ran well beyond the light trading usual for a half-session and a forward swing in rates which was wider than on any of the preceding days.

docs.lead_paragraph: A gold doblon of Uruguay issued in 1870, bearing the national arms as the chief design and said to be the only specimen of that date in existence, sold for $860 yesterday at the auction of the first part of the Waldo Newcomer collection of South American and Mexican coins held at the Morgenthau Gallery, 23 West Forty-seventh Street.

headline.main: RARE COIN BRINGS $860 AT AUCTION; Uruguayan Gold Doblon Takes Top Price as Newcomer Collection Sale Opens.
